gomodel:SYNGO_989  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2 shows immuno-EM on GIPC1 in rodent hippocampus, which is found both in the pre- and post-synapse. Fig2c shows clear immunoreactivity by light microscopy in wild type which is not present in the Gipc1 null, indicating that the antibody is specific. Fig 2f and g show immunoreactivity in the presynapse by DAB and immunogold methods respectively. Panels e and h show immunoreactivity in the postsynaptic compartment with the same two methods.. Experimental description: The immuno-EM was done on rat and mouse (M&M \"Adult male mice or Sprague-Dawley rats were anesthetized, perfused, and processed for light or electron microscopy as described previously\") the panels in Fig2 e-i are not further specified \"Ultrastructural analysis of GIPC1 in adult rodent hippocampus.\"\n\n8/7/2017 Pim\n- The lack of species information in Fig.2e-i is problematic. I have contacted the authors (moses.chao@med.nyu.edu; email dd 8/7/2017) for additional information. Answer: \"For Fig.2 the species of the tissues used in panels e-i, Images (e, f, g, h) are rat. Image (i) is mouse.\" I have made annotation to rat species." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_989" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

